<FONT CLASS="ArticleSource"><BIG>Test Server:</BIG></FONT> 
<FONT CLASS="ArticleHead"><BIG>No Triple Attack for J00!</BIG></FONT>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </FONT><FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthor">Battaile Fauber</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleTime>09/20/2001 08:23 PM CDT</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleText>
From Test server patch message:<p><B>September 20th, 6:00pm<br>-------------------------<p>** Melee Changes Update **<p>-The Triple Attack skill has been removed from rangers.  After examining the effects of this skill during actual play, and then further discussion with both the development team and our player base, it became clear that triple attack was not a necessary upgrade to the ranger class.  Rangers in their current form do damage appropriate to what we expect, and do not need additional upgrades to damage output.<p>We'll keep you updated on any further adjustment to these melee changes.</B><p><I>Moorgard adds:</I>Thanks for submitting the breaking news, Battaile! =)<p>Before you rangers get upset--whoops, <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=bdd914931ad331d84a7414348cf80d27&amp;threadid=30673">too late</a>--remember that this entire balance thing is on Test server for a reason. More tweaking is going to happen, and all affected classes should be ready for it.<p>Some rangers are already blaming this change on the complaints of rogues in that <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=8186.topic">godawful thread</a> over at The Safehouse. That's probably unfair, but it will be a hard sentiment to shake from the ranger community. Rogues (and The Safehouse, to a certain extent) are still taking the heat for one North ToV item getting nerfed, so this might result in some bad press for rogues.<p>Let's all just try to get along, people.<p><B>Updated 1:15 PM CDT</B><p>Absor responded to a ranger's question as to why triple attack was removed, and by what means Verant had come to the decision to do so:<p><B>I can't explain why we're making the changes we are making in any other way than I have. We are trying to make certain that the melee abilities of the melee and hybrid classes meet our expectations. We will make the adjustments needed to set the balance in the high level combat side of the game. In order to do that properly we can't worry about whether or not it looks like we have 'a bone thrown' to any given class. What we need to do is make the system work properly.<p>We have no intention of upsetting anyone. Not adding triple attack for rangers was something that our analysis showed to be the right decision. Before all of this goes Live we may very well have to make other adjustments.<p>We need to be able to use our Test server for testing. We really need you all to understand that we will be introducing and removing and fiddling with things on that server as a part of testing. It becomes very hard for us to do this if every adjustment is going to be seen as a 'nerf' and every addition as a promise. We certainly understand how changes like this can be a disappointment. It isn't our intent to upset anyone. But we have to adjust these changes or the point of having a Test server is lost.</B><p>Once again, I can't argue with Absor's logic. Rangers are complaining about a change that was never made to the actual game because it negates a different change that was likewise never actually made to the game.<p>Confused?<p>I suppose news sites like ours don't make Absor's job any easier (then again, why should we?). Verant does need an environment where players can test changes that the company is considering, yet players latch on to positive ones as if Verant has made them a solemn vow and furiously attack others that are seen as negative.<p>Still, I know how upset I'd be if a Test server patch message proclaimed something to the effect that monks weren't getting a new combat table after all. In fact, I'd be crestfallen. But I don't think I could blame rogues, rangers, wizards, or any other unhappy class.<p>Hard as it is for some people to believe, Verant doesn't hate certain classes and love others. They care about EverQuest as a whole, and do what they feel is in the best interests of preserving its franchise for the long haul.<p>But I suppose that's small consolation for the little ranger who wanted to be king.<p>Ah well, them's the breaks.
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
